The Project (Overview)

VentureCrowd holds an option over a property located at 495 Wynnum Road, Morningside, Queensland, with an exercise price of $4.35M due 31 March 2025.

The Fund is raising $1.5M to:

  • Obtain a Development Approval (DA) and enter into a conditional agreement with a qualified co-living management company.
  • Sell the DA-approved project before the March 2025 settlement date for an estimated $7.5M.

This is a conservative exit valuation, given an expected Net Operating Income of over $1.9M in the first year of operation.

Key Investment Highlights

  • Strong Market Demand: Driven by interstate migration, robust employment growth, and supply-led challenges, fueling the rise of the co-living housing sector in Brisbane.
  • Target Return: 30% p.a., estimated 9 to 12 month term.
  • Favorable Option Terms: Property held under an option for $4.35M+ GST, until March 2025.
  • Strategic Development: Amendment of existing Development Approval (DA) for a hotel build into a co-living project. Foundations of the planned hotel are in place, and the co-living scheme is designed to fit within the existing DA footprint. Approval expected by August/September 2024 for minor changes or January/February 2025 for a new DA.
  • Profitable Sale Prospects: Anticipates sale price, including approval, at ~$7.5M.
  • Experienced Operator: UKO, co-living real estate operators managing over 46 blocks with more than 1,500 apartments in Sydney and Melbourne, have expressed interest in the completed property.

The Future of Living - A Smart Solution to Growing Populations and Escalating Costs

Brisbane property prices have increased by 65% since 2020, almost double the Australian capital city average of 34%. New tenancy rents in Queensland have climbed faster than the national average, rising by 45% over the same period. With the cost of living on the rise, renters will prioritize affordable, central housing options with easy access to essential amenities.

Unlike traditional housing developments, co-living housing is more affordable for new entrants to the housing market, such as singles and young couples, due to shared amenities and furnished accommodations. Co-living's short-term flexibility appeals to tenants who seek fluidity in their living arrangements, attracting Australia's growing demographic of young freelancers, entrepreneurs, and remote workers.

VentureCrowd holds an option over a centrally located property in Brisbane with potential for 114 co-living studio apartments (circa 6,600 sqm net Leasable Area). Demonstrable interest from renowned co-living operator UKO has been received, with potential end-purchasers identified. A competitive sales campaign will be conducted once the DA is obtained.

The Location

Morningside, QLD

  • Population: 10,477 residents, with 41.71% in rental accommodation.
  • Median Listing Price for Units: $0.55M, increased by 10%+ in the last year.
  • Transport: Well-connected to the city by train, bus, and ferry routes.
  • Schools: Nearby private and public schools include Cannon Hill Anglican College, Morningside State School, and Balmoral State High School.
  • Recreation: Parks and green spaces such as Colmslie Recreation Reserve and Balmoral Park.

Market Drivers
Brisbane has become one of Australia’s strongest capital city housing markets, now the second-most expensive city for housing in the country, with prices jumping by 1.4% in May 2024. Rental markets remain exceptionally tight, with vacancy rates near record lows. Federal government forecasts suggest Queensland’s population will grow by more than 16% by the 2032 Brisbane Olympics, with Greater Brisbane expected to grow faster than the rest of the state.

Brisbane has become one of Australia’s strongest capital city housing markets, and according to CoreLogic, is now the second-most expensive city for housing in the country, with prices jumping by 1.4% in May 2024.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue

The Fund

The Fund is an unregistered wholesale managed investment scheme, structured as a unit trust, the trustee of which is VentureCrowd Nominees Pty Ltd (ACN 166 599 140). Investors in this tranche of funding will acquire A Class Units in the Fund at an issue price of $1.00 per Unit.

The Fund will purchase preference shares in Wynnum Rd Morningside Pty Ltd (ACN 677 549 101), which holds an option to purchase the Property.

On a liquidation event, the preference shares are entitled to be paid the capital invested in preference to ordinary shareholders and thereafter will have full participation rights with the ordinary shareholders on a pro rata basis.

The Trustee will issue Units to investors in its capacity as an authorised representative of VentureCrowd Pty Ltd (ACN 166 598 849) under AFSL No.503381.

Project Feasibility

Based on a land acquisition price of $4.35M, planning and design costs of $1.5M, and an improved land value of $7.5M, the development work forecasts a transaction profit of $1.2M after repayment of investor capital and a return of 30% p.a. The target development schedule is 11 months.

Who Can Invest?

This offer is open to wholesale and pre-approved experienced investors. If you have a wholesale investor certification, have assets of AUD $2.5 million or have a gross income of the last 2 financial years of at least AUD $250,000 per annum, this may apply to you. If you are an experienced investor with multiple investments in venture capital or property, you may be qualified by our team as a wholesale investor upon reviewing your documentation.

Risks

Whilst the directors of the Fund Manager are experienced investment managers and the senior executives of the Development Manager have substantial experience in managing property development projects, there are always risks associated with development and construction which may, either directly or indirectly, result in reduced distributions and/or a loss of some of the capital value of an investment in the Fund.

Before deciding whether to subscribe for Units, you should consider whether an investment in this Fund, the underlying asset of which will be the Property, is suitable for you. If you are in doubt as to whether you should invest, please consult a suitably qualified professional advisor.

The key risks associated with investing in the Fund are set out in the Information Memorandum attached below and include the following:

  • a downturn in the general economic and market conditions in South-East Queensland
  • unfavourable movements in interest rates, inflation or the unemployment rate
  • changes to the law (including tax laws) and accounting rules
  • industrial relations disputes and strikes
  • natural disasters, including earthquakes, fire and storm
  • social unrest, terrorist attack or war in Australia or overseas
  • no guarantee of performance or return
  • development costs and project expenditure being lower than forecast
  • issues and delays with council
  • related parties not performing
  • availability of construction funding.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Fees and Expenses

The fees and expenses payable in connection with the management of the Fund are as follows:

  • Contribution Fee: 1.1% of your investment amount in the Fund, payable upon acceptance of your investment by the Trustee
  • Origination Fee: $195,000 + GST. This is the fee the VentureCrowd Group charges for the reimbursement of costs associated with originating this opportunity and securing the Option. This fee is payable from the Fund’s assets at first close
  • Management Fee: 1.65% p.a. of the Gross Asset Value of the Fund, payable by the Fund’s assets
  • Expenses: estimated at 0.5% p.a. of the Gross Asset Value of the Fund, payable by the Fund’s assets
  • Off Market Transfer Fee (if you wish to transfer your holding to someone else): $500 + 2% of the total amount transferred, unless the buyer is identified by you in advance*

*If the buyer is identified by you in advance the 2% fee does not apply. VentureCrowd cannot guarantee a purchaser for your holding.

For a full explanation of costs and expenses, please review the IM.
